	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=11999&mid=109091918754909>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=11999&mid=109091918754909>RE: FT stacking</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=11999&mid=109091918754909#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jul 27th 5:06 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=96835><span id= >Borogove</span></a><br><span id=notbold>46 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.94]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Form of the Howler is +2 Mana regen, but Form of the Hunter has no mana regen, specifically so it will stack with Mask of the Hunter (or, of course, Mask of the Stalker, which is identical, except it can be cast indoors).<br><br>Spirit of Ash is +2 Mana regen, Oak is +4.<br><br>But yes, in general, druid self-only buffs with mana regen will not stack with each other.&nbsp;&nbsp;They also, incidentally, will not stack with the enchanter spells Gift of Insight or Gift of Brilliance, which give a small mana regen, and a mana pool increase.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
